12:05.116 --> 12:07.283
In fact,
I'm downright great at 'em.

12:07.302 --> 12:08.709
I could help you if you want.

12:08.729 --> 12:11.788
Yeah? Could you make it sound
so she thinks me,

12:11.806 --> 12:14.474
a white guy, is the one
who actually wrote it?

12:14.626 --> 12:16.142
Easy. Write this.

12:16.294 --> 12:17.736
"Dearest Margerie,

12:17.887 --> 12:19.738
"I can't wait to get home

12:19.889 --> 12:23.149
"and back that big fat ass up.

12:23.243 --> 12:25.744
"Back, back, back it up.

12:25.895 --> 12:28.304
"Back, back,
back it up.

12:28.323 --> 12:31.750
Wu Tang Clan
ain't nothing to mess with."

12:31.977 --> 12:33.234
<i> PETER:</i>
<i> Dearest Margerie,</i>

12:33.328 --> 12:35.587
<i> a lady who worked at the hotel</i>
<i> we were staying at</i>

12:35.738 --> 12:38.757
<i>had, like, the freckliest chest</i>
<i> I've ever seen.</i>

12:38.984 --> 12:40.425
<i> Yours, Vinny.</i>

12:40.576 --> 12:42.652
<i> JEROME:</i>
<i> Ultimately,</i>
<i> Vinny went his own way</i>

12:42.670 --> 12:43.595
<i> with the letter.</i>

12:43.822 --> 12:46.598
♪

12:46.825 --> 12:48.007
Hey, Muddy, I was thinking,

12:48.101 --> 12:49.675
since we made it
to the part of the story

12:49.828 --> 12:52.086
where we realize that we're not
so different from each other,

12:52.105 --> 12:53.104
we should celebrate.

12:53.256 --> 12:55.440
Yeah? What did you have in mind?

12:55.609 --> 12:57.258
I don't know. Maybe...

12:57.277 --> 12:58.259
that!

12:58.353 --> 13:00.320
♪

13:03.432 --> 13:04.699
(tires screech)

13:05.786 --> 13:07.434
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

13:07.529 --> 13:09.362
This is
a "whites only" carnival.

13:09.514 --> 13:11.531
It's okay, Vinny.
Let's get out of here.

13:11.683 --> 13:15.668
No! This is unacceptable,
and it will not stand!

13:17.856 --> 13:20.298
My friend is a human being!

13:23.953 --> 13:26.095
We demand recourse!

13:28.958 --> 13:30.124
(slurping)

13:30.143 --> 13:32.143
Unconscionable!

13:32.295 --> 13:34.203
<i> JEROME:</i>
<i> And though the trip</i>
<i> was soon over,</i>

13:34.222 --> 13:37.315
<i> a friendship was formed</i>
<i> that transcended race.</i>

13:37.466 --> 13:39.208
<i> But it would not last long.</i>

13:39.227 --> 13:40.376
What the hell?!

13:40.469 --> 13:43.404
All the pages in my songbook
are torn out!

13:45.900 --> 13:48.660
<i> PETER:</i>
<i> Dear Muddy,</i>
<i> I have something to confess.</i>

13:48.811 --> 13:50.236
<i> I stole all your songs,</i>

13:50.388 --> 13:52.146
<i> and my real name</i>
<i> is Elvis Presley.</i>

13:52.165 --> 13:53.998
That son of a bitch!

13:54.150 --> 13:56.501
Damn you, Elvis Presley!

13:56.652 --> 13:57.743
(sighs)
Oh, well.

13:57.896 --> 14:00.321
There's still an exciting future
ahead of me.

14:00.415 --> 14:03.049
This ain't the end of my story.

14:04.160 --> 14:06.327
Oh, no.
The screen's turnin' sepia.

14:06.346 --> 14:08.071
This<i> is</i> the end of my story!

14:08.164 --> 14:09.530
I got to get to a stool
for the one

14:09.591 --> 14:11.591
"old-timey Black guy musician"
photo

14:11.743 --> 14:13.576
anyone will ever know me by.

14:13.595 --> 14:17.096
<i> Muddy didn't make it to</i>
<i>the stool in time for his photo.</i>

14:17.248 --> 14:19.582
<i> Elvis never gave him</i>
<i> the credit he deserved.</i>

14:19.601 --> 14:24.011
<i> And people were</i> pissed
<i>when</i> Green Book<i> won that Oscar.</i>

14:24.030 --> 14:25.238
<i> The end.</i>

14:29.777 --> 14:32.019
♪

14:32.038 --> 14:33.596
Great story, Jerome.

14:33.689 --> 14:36.265
Elvis really was the best.

14:36.359 --> 14:38.284
Peter, is that Stewie?

14:38.436 --> 14:40.712
PETER:
Oh, yeah. Looks like
he's gonna do one next.

14:40.863 --> 14:42.046
You're gonna let the baby
do one?

14:42.198 --> 14:44.865
Oh, I'm sorry,
are<i> your</i> children funny?

14:44.885 --> 14:46.109
No.

14:46.127 --> 14:48.553
Ah, here it is.

14:48.704 --> 14:50.446
Elton John's<i> Greatest Hits,</i>

14:50.465 --> 14:53.207
a collection of songs
by the one gay guy on earth

14:53.226 --> 14:55.376
with a worse haircut
than Pete Rose.

14:55.395 --> 14:58.304
♪

14:58.398 --> 15:00.732
We'll defer
that end-of-year bonus

15:00.959 --> 15:02.233
to the following fiscal quarter,

15:02.460 --> 15:04.085
harvest the losses
on our cap gains--

15:04.087 --> 15:05.403
that's a no-brainer--
and, let's see,

15:05.630 --> 15:07.463
update
my beneficiary designations?

15:07.482 --> 15:09.482
(chuckles):
Uh, yeah, I think so.

15:09.634 --> 15:10.557
Damn, I'm good.

15:11.819 --> 15:14.971
Elton John, what the hell
do you think you're doing?!

15:15.064 --> 15:16.748
It's just a little
number crunchin', Pop.

15:16.975 --> 15:18.324
What's going on in here?

15:18.418 --> 15:20.977
Why don't you ask your son,
the tax man?

15:20.995 --> 15:22.828
I found these
under his mattress!

15:22.981 --> 15:24.163
W-2s!

15:24.315 --> 15:27.091
I-I was holding them
for a friend.

15:29.320 --> 15:30.820
Wh-Wh-What are you doin', Pop?

15:30.838 --> 15:34.173
No son of mine is gonna be
a heterosexual paper pusher.

15:34.267 --> 15:38.353
You need to be a loud-and-proud
performer like your gay old dad!

15:39.998 --> 15:42.065
(air whooshing softly)

15:49.765 --> 15:51.598
Aah! You hit me!

15:51.693 --> 15:55.178
Oh, Elton. I'm telling you this
because I love you.

15:55.196 --> 15:57.680
You'll never find someone
to love you.

15:57.699 --> 16:00.349
Not even Dolly Levi
could help you.

16:00.443 --> 16:02.351
-Who's Dolly Levi?
-(gasping)

16:02.370 --> 16:05.538
Oh, where did we go so wrong?!

16:05.690 --> 16:08.615
<i> STEWIE:</i>
<i> So Elton John collaborated</i>
<i> with Bernie Taupin,</i>

16:08.635 --> 16:11.118
<i> who would write the lyrics</i>
<i> for Elton's songs.</i>

16:11.137 --> 16:13.713
<i> Bernie was married three times</i>
<i> in a desperate bid</i>

16:13.865 --> 16:16.474
<i> to convince the world</i>
<i> he was not a homosexual.</i>

16:16.625 --> 16:18.050
(plays note)

16:18.203 --> 16:19.460
All right, Bernie,
what do you got?

16:19.479 --> 16:20.294
Uh, how 'bout this?

16:20.313 --> 16:22.129
"Yours are the sweetest eyes

16:22.223 --> 16:23.314
I've ever seen."

16:23.466 --> 16:24.482
They are?

16:25.485 --> 16:26.818
Whoa! I-I'm not gay.

16:26.969 --> 16:28.820
You're not?
Y-You just seem very...

16:28.971 --> 16:31.063
Yeah. I'm British.
We all seem that way,

16:31.157 --> 16:33.307
even if we're not
but secretly are.

16:33.326 --> 16:35.551
♪

16:35.570 --> 16:38.571
Elton, meet the best producer
in the business.

16:38.723 --> 16:41.315
Kid, how would you like to sign
with my label,

16:41.334 --> 16:43.392
Naive-Young-Talent Records.

16:43.486 --> 16:47.063
Together,
we are gonna make me millions!

16:47.081 --> 16:49.232
Sounds fair to me.
Let's get to it!

16:49.250 --> 16:51.676
<i> From then on,</i>
<i> Elton's new male producer</i>

16:51.827 --> 16:54.237
<i> rode him day and night.</i>

16:54.330 --> 16:56.663
<i>When Elton was tired of playing,</i>
<i> he'd get right behind him</i>

16:56.683 --> 16:59.333
<i> and push him on the stool</i>
<i> until he was finished.</i>

16:59.352 --> 17:00.426
<i> Sometimes Elton would cry</i>

17:00.520 --> 17:02.336
<i> because of how hard</i>
<i> he was pushing.</i>

17:02.430 --> 17:04.747
<i> But it paid off,</i>
<i> because, in the end,</i>

17:04.766 --> 17:07.266
<i> they had a massive load.</i>
<i> Of hits.</i>

17:07.360 --> 17:10.753
<i> Just a-- just a big,</i>
<i> messy load of hits.</i>

17:10.772 --> 17:13.773
<i> The night Elton John performed</i>
<i> at Dodger Stadium,</i>

17:13.925 --> 17:17.184
<i> he was so nervous, he almost</i>
<i> never left the dressing room.</i>

17:17.203 --> 17:19.370
CROWD (in distance):
Elton! Elton!

17:19.522 --> 17:21.205
Elton! Elton!

17:29.215 --> 17:30.214
Whoa, dude, no!

17:30.366 --> 17:32.216
I'm just
a straight moment of clarity.

17:32.368 --> 17:34.218
Oh, I'm sorry. I didn't, uh...

17:34.370 --> 17:36.554
<i> But his reflection</i>
<i> had walked away,</i>

17:36.705 --> 17:38.114
<i> never to return.</i>

17:38.132 --> 17:40.283
<i>And he had to do his own makeup.</i>

17:40.301 --> 17:41.208
(cheering)

17:41.227 --> 17:43.061
<i>Also, due to a scheduling error,</i>

17:43.212 --> 17:45.212
<i> the Dodgers had a game</i>
<i> that night,</i>

17:45.231 --> 17:48.232
<i> and Elton had to bat fourth</i>
<i> in the lineup.</i>

17:51.462 --> 17:54.072
<i> ANNOUNCER:</i>
<i> It's a mince-off single</i>
<i> and the Dodgers win!</i>

17:54.223 --> 17:57.558
(cheering, whooping)

17:57.652 --> 18:00.803
<i> STEWIE:</i>
<i>Elton John was heavily involved</i>
<i> in the L.A. party scene,</i>

18:00.896 --> 18:02.638
<i> and things took a dark turn</i>
<i> one night</i>

18:02.731 --> 18:05.416
<i> when he and Bernie went to</i>
<i>a party in the Hollywood Hills,</i>

18:05.568 --> 18:07.401
<i> one where you park</i>
<i> way down at the bottom</i>

18:07.420 --> 18:09.328
<i>and have to walk all the way up.</i>

18:09.480 --> 18:11.647
(panting)

18:11.666 --> 18:13.316
God, how much farther is it?

18:13.409 --> 18:14.741
I don't know.
You didn't get a TripTik.

18:14.761 --> 18:17.169
That's 'cause the rock star
doesn't get the TripTik.

18:17.322 --> 18:19.004
The writer gets the TripTik.

18:19.099 --> 18:20.656
Damn it,
here comes another person

18:20.675 --> 18:22.174
walking to the same party.

18:22.327 --> 18:24.493
Let's stop, so we don't have
to walk with him the whole way.

18:24.587 --> 18:27.105
When they said
this party was "far out,"

18:27.256 --> 18:28.422
they weren't kidding.

18:28.441 --> 18:30.333
(forced chuckling)
I know, right? Yeah.

18:30.351 --> 18:31.442
-♪
-Look, we've got to be close.

18:31.594 --> 18:33.035
I can hear the music.

18:33.095 --> 18:34.670
Damn it!
We're in the wrong canyon!

18:34.689 --> 18:35.947
Well, I'm exhausted.

18:36.098 --> 18:37.340
Come on, let's just go home.

18:37.433 --> 18:39.508
I don't know.
I kind of want to stay out.

18:39.527 --> 18:41.177
Hang on. Hey!

18:41.270 --> 18:43.937
What's the cocaine sitch like
at that party?!

18:43.957 --> 18:45.957
Enough to kill a Belushi!

18:46.108 --> 18:47.516
But you probably don't want
to come!

18:47.535 --> 18:50.019
It's a real sausage fest
over here!

18:50.037 --> 18:51.462
I'm going to that (bleep) party.

18:51.614 --> 18:54.707
Elton, if you leave me
right now, it's a big deal,

18:54.859 --> 18:57.026
because this is the time of the
story where that's a big deal.

18:57.044 --> 19:00.379
What'd you say?! I couldn't hear
you over the sound of snorting!

19:00.531 --> 19:03.457
Have fun getting home
without a TripTik, trip dick!

19:03.476 --> 19:06.886
Whoa-ho! Looks like Elton
learned how to write!

19:07.038 --> 19:08.629
(snorting)

19:08.648 --> 19:11.607
♪

19:12.968 --> 19:14.635
How is he, Doctor?

19:14.654 --> 19:17.213
Well, looks like your husband's
gonna be all right, Mr., uh...

19:17.231 --> 19:19.382
I've been married three times!
I'm Bernie Taupin!

19:19.400 --> 19:20.383
You know what,
don't worry about it.

19:20.401 --> 19:21.642
I already forgot who you are.

19:21.736 --> 19:23.068
Anyway, congratulations.

19:23.221 --> 19:25.905
Elton will be back on his knees
in no time.

19:26.057 --> 19:27.890
Look at me. At some hospital

19:27.909 --> 19:29.650
next to a Denny's
by the airport.

19:29.669 --> 19:32.411
All day long,
it's just Denny's and the jets.

19:32.563 --> 19:34.622
Wait, what'd you just say?
Say that again.

19:35.658 --> 19:37.583
The important thing is
you're alive.

19:37.677 --> 19:40.753
Thanks. Hey, what do you say we
get the ole team back together

19:40.905 --> 19:44.240
for a "what do they look like
now" credits montage?

19:44.333 --> 19:47.167
Well, we can,
but I'm not sure you'll like it.

19:47.187 --> 19:49.078
<i> STEWIE:</i>
<i> That's what I look like?!</i>

19:49.096 --> 19:51.338
<i> Who is letting me out</i>
<i> of the house like--</i>

19:51.357 --> 19:54.250
<i> Someone in the future</i>
<i> is seriously failing me!</i>

19:54.268 --> 19:57.010
<i> BRIAN:</i>
<i> Yeah, you look like a</i> Candy
Land<i> villain that came to life.</i>

19:57.030 --> 19:58.270
<i> -STEWIE: I know!</i>
<i> -You look like a Muppet</i>

19:58.423 --> 20:00.439
<i> that teaches kids</i>
<i> about being gay.</i>

20:00.591 --> 20:02.349
<i> STEWIE:</i>
<i> All right, that's enough.</i>
<i> Why are we making fun of me?</i>

20:02.368 --> 20:05.594
<i> I'm not a bad guy. Let's just</i>
<i>make fun of Sean Hannity again.</i>

20:05.613 --> 20:08.597
<i> BRIAN:</i>
<i> He looks like a guy</i>
<i> who just OD'd on Just For Men.</i>

20:08.616 --> 20:10.208
<i> STEWIE:</i>
<i> He looks like Alan Thicker.</i>

20:10.359 --> 20:11.858
<i> BRIAN:</i>
<i> He's a guy</i>
<i> whose wife yells at him</i>

20:11.953 --> 20:13.711
<i> for getting his ball powder</i>
<i> all over the bathroom.</i>

20:13.862 --> 20:15.862
<i> STEWIE:</i>
<i> All right,</i>
<i> we could do this all day.</i>

20:15.882 --> 20:19.217
<i> For more Hannity slams, go</i>
<i> to</i> Family Guy's<i> YouTube page.</i>

20:19.368 --> 20:22.053
<i> And, hey, if you think of your</i>
<i> own, leave it in the comments.</i>

20:22.204 --> 20:24.113
<i> BRIAN:</i>
<i> He's the guy</i>
<i> your mom dates twice</i>

20:24.206 --> 20:25.448
<i> and then yells at you</i>
<i> for the remote.</i>

20:25.466 --> 20:27.475
<i> STEWIE: (laughs)</i>
<i> Okay. But now we're done.</i>

20:33.124 --> 20:35.566
Well, I can't think
of a better way to end our visit

20:35.718 --> 20:39.795
than by remembering the four
lads who started a band in 1962

20:39.814 --> 20:41.405
and changed the world forever.

20:41.632 --> 20:43.890
-Steve, Dal, Bob and Robin.
-John, Paul, George and Ringo.

20:43.910 --> 20:45.892
-Who?
-Steve, Dal, Bob and Robin.

20:45.912 --> 20:46.911
The Trashmen.

20:47.062 --> 20:48.079
Oh...

